As well as the supposed homosexuality or mental handicap of certain victims of deportation.
The records of the concentration camps or detention orders established by the Gestapo had been gathered after the war for a practical purpose: to find the deported or subjected to forced labour and, eventually, to provide them with proof of their internment, in order to pave the way for their indemnification.
