Which insurance is right for me?
Car insurance, which covers the driver in the event of possible accidents, is an important expense that will depend on various factors, such as age, sex, card age, marital status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use of it, among others.
Having a car is just the beginning.
And that is, choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing the vehicle model.
First of all, we need to be clear about what we are talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insured.
This commitment is embodied in an insurance contract, which stipulates that the company receives the value of the agreed premium in exchange for being liable for the obligation to pay the compensation in case of bankruptcy.
The premium is the price of insurance, which is established taking into account various factors, such as age, sex, the age of the carne, the marital status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use given to it, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices based on the statistics, so the more likely they are to suffer an accident, the higher the fee to pay.
It is for this reason that both adults over 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, as the statistics reflect that they have a lower rate of sinestrality due to their prudence.
Also, taking into account the numbers, companies have come to the conclusion that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use given to the vehicle will influence the frequency, and thus the likelihood of having some kind of permanence.
As the frequency increases, the odds increase.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when setting the price of the premium.
It is for this reason that the driver has to study the situation well to choose that car insurance that best fits his profile.
We will expose here the most significant variables when choosing one or another type of insurance, so that it, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insured, offers you a reasonable price.
Young people under the age of 25 face various drawbacks when it comes to hiring insurance at an affordable price, such as reduced driving experience and the age of the car.
While the ideal to be well-insured is all-risk insurance, there are other cheaper options.
The most cautious drivers can opt for an entire risk with franchise, so they get insurance coverage at all risk but at a more feasible price.
This type of agreement would require the customer to pay a portion of the sinestra amount.
“The part of the amount of the sinester that the customer provides will be pre-set based on the value of the premium, which will be higher the lower the amount,” said Luis Noguera, chief executive officer in Spain of First Europe, an online insurance broker.
Another option is extended third-party insurance, so that the customer ensures protection against damage caused to third parties, although not to those caused in their own car.
In addition, it would be covered by theft, fire and vehicle loss.
A piece of advice.
If you are under the age of 25 try to be careful and avoid sinister as much as possible, as this will affect the bonus, being able to reduce the cost of insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction on the base rate owned by the company.
On the contrary, a penalty is a surcharge on that base rate.
"The bonuses and penalties will depend on the company and its benefit.
If the company has had a good year, it will be possible to increase the bonuses,” explains Noguera.
After the age of 25 drivers have it easier when it comes to hiring insurance, as the rate of sine-estrality is reduced thanks to the accumulated experience.
For this reason, it is best to hire an entire risk franchise.
“Normally, young people can’t make use of the experience previously acquired when using an accident, and even when driving,” says the director in Spain of the European company, adding that most accidents occur in the second year of driving, once the ‘fear of the novice’ has passed.
However, if the client is married but still does not have children it is preferable to negotiate insurance at all risk, as long as their economic situation allows it, of course.
For its part, marriages with children are considered by insurers as the public with the lowest rate of sinestraality, so the surcharges will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be one at all risk with franchise (which could be 300 euros), or, when a high level of bonus is available, one at third party extended from the third year of life of the vehicle.
“They carry out a more relaxed driving and have a greater purchasing power to allow themselves the luxury of taking on a larger amount of franchise,” Luis Noguera said.
For retirees it is recommended to have insurance at all risk with franchise (being this one 150 euros), or one to third party extended when you have a high level of bonus.
It must be said that car insurance is something important, not only because it covers the driver in the event of possible accidents, but also because it represents an important expense, which is why it is essential to properly study the insurance that suits us most according to our personal situation.
